"COME WITH ME"

Like tide turning, drawn by the moon, 
she had ebbed, little by little, away from me, so
that she stood once again on a lonely shore, 
watching the distance widen between us.

I asked her, in many ways, to come with me, 
before i got tired of asking.

-Marwan
